body:
I think I may be hitting this issue. I can't get the `delay` property of the `AnimationOptions` object to work. Is this really a feature, and not a bug..?

```ts
export const fadeIn = animation([
  style({ opacity: '{{ start }}' }),
  animate(200,
    style({ opacity: '{{ end }}' }))
], {
  delay: 3000,
  params: { time: '.2s', timing: 'ease-in', start: 0, end: '*' }
});

export function fade() {
  return trigger('fadeIn', [
    transition(':enter', useAnimation(fadeIn))
  ]);
}
```
